Stakeholders of water companies in Murang'a held a meeting yesterday to deliberate and try to solve issues affecting the management of water companies. This followed allegations that the county government of Murang'a was interfering with the operations of Muwasco, which is the water company of Murang'a. The governor of Murang'a mwangi wa iria has since denied those allegations and said that he was just fighting for common citizens who fall victims of the wrangles.